Interface RecordLoader

public interface RecordLoader
A class responsible for loading timeSeries objects from files.
Author:
Othonas Gkavardinas

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    double[] constructObjects​(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> tokens)
    Gets the specified values of a file as String ArrayList and transforms them to a double array.
    double[] load​(java.lang.String fileName, java.lang.String delimeter, boolean hasHeaderLine, int number)
    Loads a timeSeries from a file.

  • Method Details

    • load

      double[] load​(java.lang.String fileName, java.lang.String delimeter, boolean hasHeaderLine, int number)
      Loads a timeSeries from a file.
      Parameters:
      fileName - A String that represents the file path.
      delimeter - A String that separates values in the given file.
      hasHeaderLine - A boolean that specifies if the first line of the given file, should not be loaded.
      number - An int that represents the placement of the timeSeries in the specified file.
      Returns:
      A double array that represents the values of a timeSeries.

    • constructObjects

      double[] constructObjects​(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> tokens)
      Gets the specified values of a file as String ArrayList and transforms them to a double array.
      Parameters:
      tokens - A String ArrayList that contains the specified values.
      Returns:
      A double array representation of the given data.
